lectic\"\npolynomials, which generalize nonsymmetric Macdonald polynomials. In this\npaper, we provide the details of the construction of metaplectic polynomials in\ntype A; the general case will be handled in the sequel to this paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Aug 2018 02:21:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 29 Jul 2019 13:11:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-30"}
